of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Hannah was born in 1485, in Whitestaunton, Somerset, England. She married John Alford in 1505, in Whitestaunton, Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1530, in her hometown, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1485–1530":"1485–1530","1475–1530":"1475–1530","1509–1575":"1509–1575","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1485":"1485","1509":"1509","1505":"1505","Whitestaunton, Chard, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whitestaunton, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1485–1530":"1485–1530","1475–1530":"1475–1530","1509–1575":"1509–1575","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1485":"1485","1509":"1509","1505":"1505","Whitestaunton, Chard, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Whitestaunton, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1485–1530":"1485–1530","1475–1530":"1475–1530","1509–1575":"1509–1575","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1485":"1485","1509":"1509","1505":"1505","Whitestaunton, Chard, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Whitestaunton, Somerset, England":"Whitestaunton, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Agnes Hannah est née en 1485, à Whitestaunton, Somerset, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Joh